Program: Discovery
Title: Beagle 2 - mission to Mars
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrykj
Last Broadcast Date: 03 December 2003
A report on the Beale 2 Mars lander project. The Beagle 2 Mars lander project is part of European Space Agency's 2003 Mars Express mission. Colin Pillinger, planetary scientist at the Open University, Dr Mark Sims and others involved with the mission talk about the project and their hopes for it.